<paragraph id="IFRS15_B63B"><paranum>B63B</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IFRS 15"/><data name="paranum" value="B63B"/></prolog><body><variant id="IFRS15_B63B_V1" base="F48807177"> <p id="IFRS15_P0746">When the requirement in <xref id="IFRS15_X0762" base="F51967143" href="IFRS15_B63A.dita#IFRS15_B63A/IFRS15_B63A_V1">paragraph B63A</xref> is met, <xref base="F31716759" href="IFRS15_APPA.dita#IFRS15_APPA/IFRS15_P0508">revenue<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0341"/></ph></xref> from a sales-based or usage-based royalty shall be recognised wholly in accordance with <xref id="IFRS15_X0763" base="F51967144" href="IFRS15_B63.dita#IFRS15_B63">paragraph B63</xref>. When the requirement in paragraph B63A is not met, the requirements on variable consideration in <xref id="IFRS15_X0764" base="F51967145" href="IFRS15_g50-59.dita#IFRS15_g50-59/IFRS15_g50-59_TI">paragraphs 50&#x2013;59</xref> apply to the sales-based or usage-based royalty.</p>  </variant></body></paragraph>